SEC. 15. Section 24 of the same Act is hereby amended to read as follows:

ГўВҖВңSEC. 24.

Creation of the National Health Insurance Fund.

ГўВҖВ“ There is hereby created a National Health Insurance Fund, hereinafter referred to as the Fund, that shall consist of:

ГўВҖВң(a) Contribution from Program members;

ГўВҖВң(b) Other appropriations earmarked by the national and local governments purposely for the implementation of the Program;

ГўВҖВң(c) Subsequent appropriations provided for under Sections 46 and 47 of this Act;

ГўВҖВң(d) Donations and grants-in-aid; and

ГўВҖВң(e) All accruals thereof.ГўВҖВқ

SEC. 23. Section 34 of the same Act is hereby amended to read as follows:

ГўВҖВңSEC. 34.

Provider Payment Mechanisms.

ГўВҖВ“ The following mechanisms for public and private providers shall he allowed in the Program:

ГўВҖВң(a) Fee-for-service payments ГўВҖВ“ payments made by the Corporation for professional fees or hospital charges, or both, based on arrangements with health care providers. This fee shall be based on a schedule to be established by the Board which shall be reviewed periodically but hot less than every three (3) years;

ГўВҖВң(b) Capitation of health care professionals and facilities, or networks of the same including HMOs, medical cooperatives, and other legally formed health service groups;

ГўВҖВң(c) Case-based payment;

ГўВҖВң(d) Global budget; and

ГўВҖВң(e) Such other provider payment mechanisms that may be determined and adopted by the Corporation.

ГўВҖВңSubject to the approval of the Board, the Corporation may adopt other payment mechanism that are most beneficial to the members and the Corporation.
